      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">42.709-7</ph> Contract clause.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d2537e8" class="- topic/p ">Use the clause at <xref href="52.242-3.dita#FAR_52_242_3"
                  base="FAR_52_242_3"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.242-3</xref>, Penalties for
Unallowable Costs, in all solicitations and contracts over $800,000
except fixed-price contracts without cost incentives or any firm-fixed-price
contract for the purchase of <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>commercial
products or commercial <?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 42.709-7 by removing the text “commercial items” and adding “commercial products or commercial services” in its place.?>services.</ph> Generally, covered contracts
are those which contain one of the clauses at <xref href="52.216-7.dita#FAR_52_216_7"
                  base="FAR_52_216_7"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.216-7</xref>, <xref href="52.216-16.dita#FAR_52_216_16"
                  base="FAR_52_216_16"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.216-16</xref>, or <xref href="52.216-17.dita#FAR_52_216_17"
                  base="FAR_52_216_17"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.216-17</xref>, or a similar
clause from an executive agency’s supplement to the FAR.</p>
